data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value:
Linux Tips: By default, root has permissions to run dmidecode. If you are running auto-discover as non-root user, you would need following in your /etc/sudoers file:
%your-group-here ALL = (ALL) NOPASSWD:/usr/sbin/dmidecode
If this permission is missing, auto-discovery client would not be able to find out hardware, manufacturer and serial #, CPU info etc. Also, you might need to comment out "Default requiretty" line in /etc/sudoers file.

data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value: Windows Tips: If you are logged in as a domain user who has rights to run wmi query remotely on the machines being discovered, you don’t have to enter your credentials, Otherwise enter credentials for user who has permissions in form of domain\username and password.
